                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.402,
                                "stop": 12.642,
                                "byte_start": 62318,
                                "byte_stop": 79245,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.642,
                                "stop": 20.743,
                                "byte_start": 79245,
                                "byte_stop": 111741,
                                "text": "In May of 1999 the respondent, Carlos Dominguez Benitez, agreed to sell methamphetamine to a federal informant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.743,
                                "stop": 30.497,
                                "byte_start": 111741,
                                "byte_stop": 150716,
                                "text": "Dominguez was arrested, confessed, and faced federal drug charges that carried a statutory and mandatory minimum sentence of ten years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.497,
                                "stop": 42.268,
                                "byte_start": 150716,
                                "byte_stop": 197841,
                                "text": "The prosecutor agreed to recommend that Dominguez escaped the mandatory minimum sentence by qualifying for a so-called safety valve that another statutory provision makes available."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.268,
                                "stop": 45.827,
                                "byte_start": 197841,
                                "byte_stop": 212052,
                                "text": "Dominguez pleaded guilty under that agreement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.827,
                                "stop": 54.94,
                                "byte_start": 212052,
                                "byte_stop": 248519,
                                "text": "The written plea agreement contained the warning that Dominguez could not withdraw his plea if the Court departed from the party\u2019s recommendation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.94,
                                "stop": 72.133,
                                "byte_start": 248519,
                                "byte_stop": 317273,
                                "text": "The District Court should have given Dominguez the same warning orally again in the plea colloquy for Rule 11 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure require the court to give that warning, but the District Court mistakenly failed to give it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.133,
                                "stop": 80.047,
                                "byte_start": 317273,
                                "byte_stop": 348933,
                                "text": "The Court and counsel later learned that Dominguez had prior convictions that disqualified him for the safety valve."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.047,
                                "stop": 88.404,
                                "byte_start": 348933,
                                "byte_stop": 382370,
                                "text": "The Court therefore departed from the recommendation of the plea agreement and imposed the mandatory 10-year minimum sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.404,
                                "stop": 117.739,
                                "byte_start": 382370,
                                "byte_stop": 499712,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit reversed holding that although Dominguez had not timely objected to the District Court\u2019s failure to warn that he could not withdraw his guilty plea, the failure to give the warning in violation of Rule 11 was plain error that effected Dominguez\u2019s substantial rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.739,
                                "stop": 127.381,
                                "byte_start": 499712,
                                "byte_stop": 538269,
                                "text": "The Court held that was enough that the error was not minor or technical and that Dominguez did not understand the rights at issue when he pleaded guilty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.381,
                                "stop": 136.004,
                                "byte_start": 538269,
                                "byte_stop": 572750,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to consider the showing a defendant must make to obtain relief for unpreserved Rule 11 error."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.004,
                                "stop": 142.299,
                                "byte_start": 572750,
                                "byte_stop": 597932,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we vacate and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.299,
                                "stop": 160.932,
                                "byte_start": 597932,
                                "byte_stop": 672434,
                                "text": "We recently held in United States v. Vonn that a defendant who does not object to a Rule 11 error at trial must satisfy the plain error standard of the United States v. Olano which requires, among other things, that an error affect a defendant\u2019s substantial rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.932,
                                "stop": 171.796,
                                "byte_start": 672434,
                                "byte_stop": 715901,
                                "text": "The phrase substantial rights, usually means that an error must have prejudicial effect on the outcome of a proceeding and we see no reason to depart from that general meaning in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.796,
                                "stop": 178.449,
                                "byte_start": 715901,
                                "byte_stop": 742546,
                                "text": "We apply a standard we have used in other cases where a defendant must establish prejudice or materiality."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.449,
                                "stop": 185.506,
                                "byte_start": 742546,
                                "byte_stop": 770759,
                                "text": "Dominguez must show a reasonable probability, but for the error he would not have entered the guilty plea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.506,
                                "stop": 199.984,
                                "byte_start": 770759,
                                "byte_stop": 828646,
                                "text": "The standard satisfies the policy of the plain error rule to encourage timely objections and it also respects that particular importance of the finality of guilty pleas which are indispensable to the modern criminal justice system."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.984,
                                "stop": 220.7,
                                "byte_start": 828646,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
